\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Cloud computing has revolutionized the way organizations manage and deploy IT resources, providing scalable access to computing services such as servers, storage, databases, networking, software, and analytics over the internet ("the cloud"). This technology enables businesses to operate more efficiently by reducing IT overhead and costs through shared resources. Key services include Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS), Platform as a Service (PaaS), and Software as a Service (SaaS). Major providers like Amazon Web Services, Microsoft Azure, and Google Cloud Platform offer robust solutions that support a wide range of applications, from data processing to artificial intelligence and machine learning. Cloud computing has become essential in disaster recovery, data backup, and global data access, facilitating innovation and agility across industries.}